AI models aren’t all the same.

A lot of people think they are. They assume every AI has the same limits, and that a prompt that works on one should work on all.

That’s not how it works.

Every model is built differently. Some are good at creative writing but terrible at math. Others can write code but give shallow summaries. Their training data and design give each one unique strengths and weaknesses. (1/2)
